Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that `PortMap.getIO` applied to `RelIO.liftFinf n f` at port `i` equals `f i`.

Let me trace through the definitions:
- `RelIO.liftFinf n f` creates an `AssocList` from `fin_range n` mapped with `λ i => ⟨↑i.toNat, f i⟩`
- I need to show that looking up port `i` in this map gives `f i`

The key is that `fin_range n` contains all `Fin n` values (by `fin_in_fin_range`), so `i` will be found in the list, and its associated value will be `f i`.

```lean
theorem RelIO.liftFinf_get {S} {n : Nat} {i : Fin n} {f : Fin n → RelIO S}:
  (RelIO.liftFinf n f).getIO i = f i := by
    dsimp [liftFinf]
    have h := fin_in_fin_range n i
    simp only [List.toList_toAssocList, AssocList.getIO_eq_getD]
    induction fin_range n with
    | nil => simp at h
    | cons hd tl ih =>
      simp at h
      cases h with
      | inl heq =>
        subst heq
        simp [AssocList.getD]
      | inr hmem =>
        simp [AssocList.getD]
        split
        · rfl
        · exact ih hmem
```
